title: I love Google Maps for all the planning but I use Apple Maps for navigation.
text:
I love Google Maps for all the planning, reviewing, and finding places but for step-by-step navigation, I use Apple Maps.

I travel a lot for my business. Google Maps is confusing when making a turn or taking an exit, specifically when we have 2-3 exits together on 3 different roads, Google Maps does not have clear directions, and sometimes time stops working at the turns, and no clear directions on which roads to merge to. Apple Maps does a good job of step-by-step Navigation, and zooming the area, so you know exactly what line to stay in and what road to take. Apple even guides us under the pass which line to stay on on and where to turn.
